10:19.820 --> 10:21.367
PLEASE GET OUT HERE.
GOOD-BYE.

10:21.480 --> 10:22.299
I LOVE YOU.
- BYE, RYAN!

10:22.410 --> 10:24.378
- MOM!

10:31.110 --> 10:34.318
[both laughing]

10:34.420 --> 10:36.285
_ UH--
- THAT'S MY MOM.

10:36.390 --> 10:38.119
- YOU STOLE MY SHIRT
SO I--

10:45.610 --> 10:47.601
- HEY, CROSBY.

10:47.710 --> 10:49.120
CROSBY!

10:49.230 --> 10:50.151
HEY!

10:53.370 --> 10:54.576
HEY.

10:54.680 --> 10:56.238
- HEY.
- WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

10:56.340 --> 10:57.819
I'M GONE FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.
THE PLACE IS A DISASTER AREA.

10:57.930 --> 11:00.069
- GOOD MORNING TO YOU TOO.

11:00.170 --> 11:01.728
- WHAT, IS THIS A JOKE?
WHAT HAPPENED?

11:01.830 --> 11:03.718
- THE DAVE RAY TRIO HAPPENED.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.058
THOSE JAZZ NERDS,
THEY KNOW HOW TO PARTY, MAN.

11:05.180 --> 11:07.136
THEY TURNED INTO GREMLINS
LAST NIGHT.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.581
- WHERE'S AMBER?
- AMBER TEXTED ME.

11:08.700 --> 11:09.928
SHE OVERSLEPT.

11:10.040 --> 11:11.359
I TOLD HER JUST
TO SHOW UP AT LUNCH.

11:11.460 --> 11:12.734
AND IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

11:12.840 --> 11:14.319
- OH, IT'S FINE FOR HER
TO COME IN LATE IN THE DAY

11:14.430 --> 11:15.385
AND THEN JUST GONNA SIT HERE.

11:15.500 --> 11:17.183
- IT'S FINE.
- CROSBY, THAT IS UNACCEPTABLE!

11:17.290 --> 11:19.804
YOU CAN'T LET HER SKATE BY
'CAUSE SHE'S A FAMILY MEMBER.

11:19.920 --> 11:21.296
- OKAY. I'M SORRY.
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:21.400 --> 11:22.628
- I'M SORRY. I'M SORRY.
- I WANT YOU TO COME DOWN HERE.

11:22.750 --> 11:23.603
- YOU'RE RIGHT.
- AND I WANT YOU TO HELP ME

11:23.710 --> 11:24.847
CLEAN THIS.
LOOK AT THAT.

11:24.960 --> 11:27.645
THAT'S REAL NICE, ISN'T IT?

11:27.750 --> 11:29.570
TELL YOU WHAT.
YOU CLEAN IT UP.

11:29.680 --> 11:31.432
- I WILL CLEAN IT UP.
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT?

11:31.550 --> 11:32.949
- I WILL.

11:33.070 --> 11:33.923
[clattering,
glass breaking]

11:34.030 --> 11:38.990
LEAVE IT.
I'LL GET THAT TOO.

11:44.040 --> 11:46.861
- CAMILLE, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO ALL OF THAT.

11:46.980 --> 11:48.698
YOU CAN LEAVE IT.
- OH, THAT'S OKAY.

11:48.810 --> 11:50.118
I DON'T MIND.
I MEAN, I'M HERE TO HELP.

11:50.220 --> 11:53.109
- I KNOW, BUT IT'S ACTUALLY
MAX'S JOB.

11:53.220 --> 11:54.152
- OH.

11:54.260 --> 11:56.296
- HE--WE'RE ON
A WHOLE STICKER SYSTEM

11:56.400 --> 11:58.914
SO IT SORT OF GIVES HIM
INCENTIVE TO DO--

11:59.020 --> 11:59.918
- OF COURSE.
- YOU KNOW.

12:00.020 --> 12:01.055
- YEAH.
- BUT THANKS.

12:01.160 --> 12:02.263
- OKAY.
SO CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?

12:02.370 --> 12:04.509
- HOW ABOUT A BIG JUG OF WINE?
[laughter]

12:04.620 --> 12:05.996
SHOULD HIT THE SPOT
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

12:06.100 --> 12:07.328
- YEAH, YOU WISH.
- I KNOW.

12:07.450 --> 12:09.202
IT'S JUST SORT OF IRONIC
I CAN'T HAVE ANY ALCOHOL

12:09.310 --> 12:10.823
CONSIDERING I'M ABOUT
TO PUMP POISON INTO MY BODY

12:10.930 --> 12:13.819
IN THE NEXT COUPLE OF DAYS.

12:13.940 --> 12:15.419
- YOU KNOW,
I HAVE A FRIEND

12:15.520 --> 12:18.409
WHO RECENTLY WENT THROUGH CHEMO.
- OH, YEAH? HOW ARE THEY DOING?

12:18.530 --> 12:20.179
- SHE'S DOING GREAT.
- REALLY?

12:20.290 --> 12:22.429
- 18 MONTHS NOW, CANCER-FREE.
- THAT'S GREAT.

12:22.530 --> 12:23.622
- SO BUT ANYWAY,
SHE SAID THAT

12:23.740 --> 12:26.777
IT'S BEST NOT TO THINK OF IT
AS POISON

12:26.880 --> 12:30.327
BUT MORE LIKE
A PLATOON OF SOLDIERS

12:30.430 --> 12:31.533
THAT HAVE ENTERED
YOUR BLOOD STREAM TO--

12:31.640 --> 12:34.985
both: FIGHT THE ENEMY...
- DISEASE.

12:35.090 --> 12:37.229
- I'VE READ ALL THE PAMPHLETS.

12:41.480 --> 12:42.754
- I HATE THIS.

12:42.860 --> 12:44.748
THE WHOLE REASON I GOT HIM
INVOLVED IN BASEBALL

12:44.860 --> 12:45.895
WAS SO HE COULD MAKE
SOME FRIENDS.

12:46.000 --> 12:47.615
- I KNOW.
- HOW COULD THEY NOT INVITE HIM?

12:47.730 --> 12:50.198
- HE'S NEW.
KIDS HAVE GROUPS, CLIQUES.

12:50.320 --> 12:51.764
I'M SURE HE'LL, YOU KNOW,
INVITED SOON.

12:51.870 --> 12:54.145
- YOU DON'T THINK
IT'S BECAUSE HE'S--

12:54.250 --> 12:56.286
- HE'S WHAT?
- BE-BECAUSE--

12:56.390 --> 12:57.618
- BECAUSE HE'S LATINO?
- YES, BECAUSE--

12:57.740 --> 12:59.116
I DON'T KNOW,
BECAUSE KIDS ARE WEIRD.

13:01.950 --> 13:05.568
WOULD HAVE THOUGHT
TO INVITE HIM.

13:11.130 --> 13:11.676
- WHAT?
- NOTHING.

13:11.790 --> 13:13.951
- HEY, BUD.

13:14.060 --> 13:15.789
YOUR MOM AND I WERE
JUST TALKING THAT YOU KNOW,

13:15.890 --> 13:17.755
YOU HAVEN'T HAD ANYBODY OVER
TO THE HOUSE YET.

13:17.860 --> 13:20.340
YOU THINK MAYBE YOU MIGHT
WANT TO, YOU KNOW,

13:20.450 --> 13:21.860
HAVE A BUDDY OVER
FOR A PLAYDATE OR--

13:21.970 --> 13:24.245
- PLAYDATE? ISN'T THAT
FOR, LIKE, FOR LITTLE KIDS?

13:24.350 --> 13:25.510
- OH, YEAH. NO.
- OH, YEAH, NO. IT IS.

13:25.630 --> 13:26.699
SO NOT A PLAYDATE.
A HANG-OUT.

13:26.800 --> 13:27.789
- HANG-OUT.
- YEAH.

13:27.910 --> 13:29.719
WOULD YOU BE INTO THAT?
- SURE.

13:29.840 --> 13:32.240
- GREAT.
- COOL.

13:32.360 --> 13:34.180
- WHO SHOULD WE INVITE?
- MAYBE MIGUEL.

13:34.290 --> 13:35.427
- OKAY.
- I DON'T KNOW MIGUEL.

13:35.530 --> 13:37.942
WHICH ONE'S--
- IS HE ON THE BASEBALL TEAM?

13:38.050 --> 13:41.019
- NO, HE USED TO LIVE
IN THE APARTMENT ABOVE MINE.

13:41.130 --> 13:42.119
- OH, YOU--
[groans]

13:42.230 --> 13:44.437
YOU MEAN IN
THE OLD NEIGHBORHOOD.

13:44.540 --> 13:46.189
- YEAH.
HE'S COOL.

13:46.300 --> 13:48.712
- YEAH, WELL,
WE'LL LOOK INTO IT.

13:48.820 --> 13:49.263
- GREAT.

13:54.590 --> 13:57.411
- CAN WE DO THAT?

13:59.180 --> 14:04.140
- WELL, THESE ARE JOB PROSPECTS
COURTESY OF THE V.A.

14:04.250 --> 14:05.046
HERE YOU GO.

14:05.150 --> 14:06.242
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:06.360 --> 14:08.385
YOU COULD PUT IN
AN APPLICATION IN HERE.

14:08.500 --> 14:09.831
AMBER USED TO WORK HERE.
SHE LIKED IT.

14:09.950 --> 14:11.633
SHE'LL PUT IN
A GOOD WORD FOR YOU.

14:11.740 --> 14:12.729
- YOU'RE REALLY INVESTED

14:12.850 --> 14:14.772
IN MY EMPLOYMENT SITUATION,
I SEE.

14:14.880 --> 14:16.017
- YEAH, I MEAN, IT'S--

14:16.130 --> 14:17.438
IT'S JUST GREAT TO HAVE
SOMEWHERE TO GO

14:17.540 --> 14:20.191
IN THE MORNING
OR A REASON TO GET UP.

14:20.300 --> 14:22.473
JUST MAKES YOU FEEL BETTER
ABOUT YOURSELF.

14:22.580 --> 14:24.127
BELIEVE ME, I KNOW.

14:24.240 --> 14:26.026
- OKAY, I'LL--
I'LL TAKE A LOOK.

14:26.140 --> 14:27.164
SPRINKLER TECHNICIAN,

14:27.280 --> 14:29.032
BERLIN-MIRO
LANDSCAPE ARCHITECTURE.

14:29.140 --> 14:30.209
STARTING SALARY--

14:30.310 --> 14:33.063
WOW, THAT'S LOW.

14:33.180 --> 14:34.693
- YEAH, WELL, OKAY.
THAT'S NOT A GOOD ONE THERE.

14:34.800 --> 14:36.028
BUT CHECK OUT THE OTHER ONES.

14:36.150 --> 14:38.903
- UH, NORELL FAMILY FARMS,
IRRIGATION CONSULTANT

14:39.010 --> 14:41.808
FOR MID-SIZED WHEAT FARM.

14:41.910 --> 14:43.116
- WHEAT.

14:43.220 --> 14:44.255
KID FROM WYOMING...

14:44.360 --> 14:48.228
MUST KNOW SOMETHING
ABOUT WHEAT.

14:48.330 --> 14:49.911
- YEAH, I DO KNOW
A LITTLE SOMETHING

14:50.020 --> 14:51.499
ABOUT PLANTING WHEAT,
BUT NOT FROM WYOMING.

14:51.610 --> 14:52.838
- YEAH, WHERE?

14:52.960 --> 14:54.916
- WELL, ONE OF MY JOBS
IN AFGHANISTAN

14:55.030 --> 14:56.292
WAS TO TALK
TO THE LOCAL FARMERS THERE.

14:56.410 --> 14:59.026
WE'D OFFER THEM SEEDS,
FERTILIZER, BETTER IRRIGATION.

14:59.130 --> 15:00.927
TRY TO GAIN THEIR TRUST,
YOU KNOW.

15:01.030 --> 15:02.201
WIN THE HEARTS AND MINDS.

15:02.310 --> 15:05.609
AND THEN, YOU KNOW,
WE WANTED THEM EVENTUALLY

15:05.730 --> 15:07.869
TO SWITCH OUT THEIR OPIUM PLANTS
FOR WHEAT CROPS.

15:07.970 --> 15:09.699
- MM-HMM.
HOW'D IT WORK OUT?

15:09.800 --> 15:12.451
- IT DIDN'T ALWAYS WORK OUT
SO GOOD.

15:13.940 --> 15:17.319
- WHAT HAPPENED?

15:17.430 --> 15:21.014
- WE MET THIS ONE OPIUM FARMER
OUTSIDE OF MARJAH,

15:21.120 --> 15:24.180
AND WE WORKED ON THIS GUY
FOR A WHILE.

15:24.300 --> 15:27.087
AND THEN FINALLY HE AGREED
TO PLANT THE WHEAT.

15:27.200 --> 15:29.054
A COUPLE OF WEEKS
AFTER WE HELPED HIM

15:29.160 --> 15:33.438
SWITCH OUT THE POPPY PLANTS,

15:33.550 --> 15:36.439
HE WAS KILLED.

15:38.100 --> 15:40.512
UH, I GUESS THEY WERE SENDING

15:40.620 --> 15:44.249
A MESSAGE TO THE REST
OF THE FARMERS.

15:44.350 --> 15:47.035
- OH.
THAT'S TOUGH.

15:47.150 --> 15:49.357
- WE KILLED THAT GUY, ZEEK.

15:49.460 --> 15:51.906
WE DIDN'T DROP ANY BOMBS
OR PULL ANY TRIGGER,

15:52.020 --> 15:55.945
BUT WE KILLED THAT GUY.

16:08.100 --> 16:09.715
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS.

16:09.830 --> 16:12.469
TRY AGAIN UP HERE.

16:14.140 --> 16:15.346
- CAN I GET SOMETHING FOR YOU?

16:18.320 --> 16:19.799
- IT'S UP HERE.
- OH. [laughs]

16:19.900 --> 16:21.481
- IT PROBABLY...
- I MOVED IT. I'M SORRY.

16:21.600 --> 16:24.114
YOU KNOW, I FIGURED
WITH YOUR STITCHES,

16:24.220 --> 16:25.664
YOU KNOW, YOU WOULDN'T
BE ABLE TO REACH.

16:25.770 --> 16:26.668
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH, CAMILLE.

16:26.770 --> 16:27.805
THAT'S GREAT.
- SURE.

16:27.910 --> 16:30.151
AND I'LL GET THE WATER.
- THANK YOU.

16:30.260 --> 16:31.773
[stove clicks]
OKAY.

16:31.880 --> 16:34.940
- IS THAT SUGAR?

16:35.060 --> 16:36.812
- YEAH.
- DON'T YOU HAVE ANY STEVIA?

16:36.920 --> 16:39.502
- I DON'T HAVE STEVIA HERE.
I DON'T USUALLY USE IT.

16:39.610 --> 16:41.020
- WELL, IT'S ACTUALLY GOOD
FOR YOU.

16:41.130 --> 16:42.336
[doorbell rings]
STEVIA, IT'S A NUTRIENT.

16:42.440 --> 16:44.579
- IT'S ONLY ONE SCOOP.
OKAY.

16:44.690 --> 16:46.476
- IS THAT YOUR DOOR?
- YOU'RE RIGHT. THAT'S MY DOOR.

16:46.590 --> 16:47.659
I'LL GET IT.
- OKAY--NO, NO, NO.

16:47.760 --> 16:49.034
I'VE GOT IT.
I'VE GOT IT.

16:49.140 --> 16:50.175
- [sighs]

16:50.280 --> 16:52.202
- OH, HI.
- HI, WE'RE THE LESSINGS,

16:52.320 --> 16:53.412
ADAM AND KRISTINA'S FRIEND'S.
- OF COURSE YOU ARE.

16:53.520 --> 16:54.521
I REMEMBER YOU.
- SHE KNOWS WHO WE ARE.

16:54.630 --> 16:56.791
[door closes]
CAMILLE, WHERE IS SHE?

16:56.910 --> 16:57.979
WHERE'S OUR GIRL?

16:58.080 --> 16:59.217
- STOP IT, PHIL.
HE DOES THIS.

16:59.320 --> 17:01.254
HE'S EXCITED BECAUSE
SHE'S LIKE FAMILY TO US.

17:01.360 --> 17:03.214
- IT'S OKAY. COME IN.
KRIS?

17:03.330 --> 17:04.354
- OH.
[laughs] HEY.

17:04.470 --> 17:07.052
- HI.
- THANKS FOR THAT, CAMILLE.

17:07.160 --> 17:08.229
- SURE.
- SORRY TO BARGE IN LIKE THIS.

17:08.330 --> 17:09.843
WE WANTED TO SEE
HOW YOU WERE DOING.

17:09.950 --> 17:11.463
- I'M GOOD.
I'M HOME.

17:11.580 --> 17:14.231
OH, AND YOU BROUGHT A CHICKEN.
- WE'RE HERE FOR YOU, KRISTINA.

17:14.340 --> 17:15.193
- THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

17:15.310 --> 17:17.335
THIS IS--THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

17:17.450 --> 17:18.269
THANK YOU.

17:18.380 --> 17:19.267
LET'S SEE WHERE I'M GONNA PUT--

17:19.380 --> 17:20.278
OKAY.
- OH, YOU GOT A FEW.

17:20.380 --> 17:21.517
[chuckles]
- THANK YOU. YEAH.

17:21.620 --> 17:22.894
A LOT OF CHICKEN.

17:23.000 --> 17:24.274
- IT'S GOOD.
- THANK YOU. YEAH.

17:24.380 --> 17:26.894
YOU KNOW.
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

17:27.010 --> 17:28.170
EVERYTHING GOOD?
- YEAH.

17:28.280 --> 17:29.451
- I'M GLAD TO SEE
YOU'RE BACK TOGETHER.

17:29.560 --> 17:30.902
- OH, YEAH, WELL,
WE'RE IN COUNSELING, YOU KNOW.

17:31.010 --> 17:33.456
- SEX THERAPY.
- CAN'T HAVE THAT--

17:33.560 --> 17:35.562
THAT'S VERY IMPORTANT.
- IT IS.

17:35.670 --> 17:38.047
- SO YOU KNOW WHAT,
I ACT UALLY--

17:38.160 --> 17:40.151
IT'S HER NAPTIME,
AND I WISH

17:40.260 --> 17:41.397
I COULD STAY
AND VISIT LONGER.

17:41.500 --> 17:42.637
AND THANK YOU FOR--
- OH, I'LL DO THAT, KRIS.

17:42.750 --> 17:44.081
- I'M GONNA TAKE HER UP.
- NO, I'VE GOT HER.

17:44.200 --> 17:45.428
- CAMILLE, I GOT IT.
- VISIT WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

17:45.540 --> 17:48.543
- THANK YOU.
- NO, REALLY, OF COURSE.

17:48.650 --> 17:49.548
- OKAY.

17:49.650 --> 17:51.129
- YOU STAY,
VISIT WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

17:51.240 --> 17:51.990
- THANK YOU.
- SAY "BYE-BYE."

17:52.100 --> 17:52.759
- BYE.
- BYE, HONEY.

17:52.860 --> 17:53.997
- HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?

17:54.100 --> 17:56.204
- I'M GOOD. I'M GOOD.

17:56.310 --> 17:57.277
I MEAN,
THIS WAS A SURPRISE--

17:57.380 --> 17:58.199
- [sobbing]
I'M SORRY.

17:58.310 --> 17:59.686
- OH, SUZE.
IT'S OKAY.

17:59.800 --> 18:03.076
- I'M SORRY. I TOLD MYSELF
I WASN'T GONNA DO THIS.

18:03.180 --> 18:04.727
- AWW, IT'S OKAY.
- I'M SORRY.

18:04.840 --> 18:06.239
- OH! I'M A...

18:06.360 --> 18:07.691
A LITTLE SORE.
- [gaSPSI

18:07.810 --> 18:08.879
OH, MY GOD.
- IT'S OKAY.

18:08.980 --> 18:10.595
OH, MY--I'M SORRY.
- IT'S OKAY.

18:10.710 --> 18:13.395
- JUST A-A GENTLE, GENTLE HUG.
- OKAY.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.183
- [sobbing]
BE CAREFUL. DON'T TOUCH HER.

18:15.300 --> 18:16.050
- CAN I GET YOU A TEA
OR SOMETHING?

18:16.160 --> 18:17.536
YOU GUYS WANT ANYTHING TO EAT?

18:17.640 --> 18:19.369
- IT'S JUST NOT RIGHT.
- I WOULD LOVE A TEA, ACTUALLY.

18:19.470 --> 18:20.505
- WANT SOME CHICKEN?
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE A SEAT?

18:20.610 --> 18:22.259
OKAY?
- DO YOU HAVE ENGLISH BREAKFAST?

18:25.650 --> 18:27.709
- I JUST SPOKE
TO THE SOCIAL WORKER.

18:27.830 --> 18:29.138
- AND?

18:29.240 --> 18:30.207
- AND SHE DOESN'T THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

18:30.310 --> 18:32.198
SHE THINKS WE SHOULD
KEEP WORKING ON

18:32.310 --> 18:33.208
ESTABLISHING HIM HERE.

18:33.310 --> 18:35.790
NOT OPEN UP OLD WOUNDS.

18:35.900 --> 18:40.769
- WHICH IS WHAT WE EXPECTED,
SO NO MIGUEL.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.622
- NO.
- WHAT?

18:42.740 --> 18:43.900
- I THINK WE SHOULD DO IT
ANYWAY.

18:44.010 --> 18:45.284
I THINK THAT IT WOULD BE
REALLY GOOD.

18:45.400 --> 18:47.539
- HONEY, THE SOCIAL WORKER
SAID IT'S A BAD IDEA.

18:47.640 --> 18:48.732
- SHE DIDN'T SAY
WE COULDN'T DO IT.

18:48.850 --> 18:50.010
- ARE YOU "LAWYERING" ME?

18:50.120 --> 18:51.121
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS?

18:51.230 --> 18:52.367
- I'M VICTOR'S MOM-ING YOU.

18:52.470 --> 18:53.812
AND I THINK THAT MY OPINION
SHOULD WEIGH

18:53.920 --> 18:55.433
AS MUCH AS HERS.
- [sighs]

18:55.540 --> 18:57.428
WE SHOULD BE HELPING VICTOR
ESTABLISH NEW FRIENDSHIPS.

18:57.550 --> 18:58.676
THAT'S WHAT WE
SHOULD BE DOING RIGHT NOW.

18:58.790 --> 19:01.236
- I KNOW, BUT HE NEEDS
A FRIEND RIGHT NOW.

19:01.340 --> 19:02.375
HE JUST NEEDS A FRIEND.

19:02.480 --> 19:04.300
- HE'S GONNA MAKE FRIENDS.
HE JUST--

19:04.410 --> 19:05.581
- BABE, HE WAS
REALLY PRETTY HEARTBROKEN.

19:05.690 --> 19:09.069
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN IT
WHEN THEY LEFT HIM OUT.

19:09.180 --> 19:13.002
I'M TELLING YOU
HE NEEDS THIS.

19:13.110 --> 19:16.147
- OKAY.

19:17.120 --> 19:19.429
- OKAY.

19:19.530 --> 19:20.838
- GOOD TO SEE YOU.
OKAY, BRIAN. TAKE CARE.

19:20.950 --> 19:22.394
YEAH.
- DAD.

19:22.500 --> 19:23.603
- SARAH. GOOD HEAVENS.
- [laughs]

19:23.710 --> 19:26.122
- HI, HOW ARE YOU?
- SO SARAH BRAVERMAN.

19:26.230 --> 19:27.436
GIVE ME A KISS.
- MWAH.

19:27.540 --> 19:29.053
- HI, SWEETHEART.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:29.160 --> 19:30.366
- WELL, I WANTED TO SEE
WHERE YOU WORK,

19:30.470 --> 19:33.030
AND ALSO MARK AND I HAVE
ALL THESE DOUBLES OF THINGS

19:33.130 --> 19:35.371
NOW THAT WE MOVED IN TOGETHER.
- HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.

19:35.480 --> 19:36.640
- COFFEEMAKER AND STUFF.
- THANK YOU, HONEY.

19:36.760 --> 19:38.580
SAMMY, SAMMY, SAMMY.
I WANT YOU TO MEET SOMEBODY.

19:38.690 --> 19:40.851
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER,
SARAH BRAVERMAN.

19:40.970 --> 19:41.994
- HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.

19:42.110 --> 19:42.553
- SAMMY WAS A PILOT.
HE GOT SHOT DOWN.

19:42.660 --> 19:44.241
- SARAH, HI.

19:44.350 --> 19:45.419
WELL, WE HEAR A TON
ABOUT YOU AROUND HERE.

19:45.520 --> 19:47.556
YOUNG FIANCE AND THE KIDS.
- THAT--YEAH.

19:47.660 --> 19:50.458
- SHE'S PRETTY THOUGH, HUH?
- OH, YES.

19:50.560 --> 19:51.766
- HEY, ZACH.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

19:51.880 --> 19:53.211
- ZACH.
I WANT YOU TO MEET SOMEBODY.

19:53.330 --> 19:54.729
ZACH'S A WORLD WAR II VET.

19:54.840 --> 19:56.159
- WELL, HI, THERE, HONEY.

19:56.260 --> 19:57.284
- HI, THERE.
- OKAY, THAT'S GOOD.

19:57.400 --> 19:59.982
HE'S A LADIES MAN.
- [laughs]

20:00.090 --> 20:01.079
AND THEN--HENRY!
HENRY, LOOK.

20:01.200 --> 20:03.509
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER, SARAH.
- HI.

20:03.610 --> 20:05.293
- YOUR DAD DOESN'T KNOW CRAP
ABOUT THE GAME OF BASEBALL.

20:05.410 --> 20:07.196
BUT HE'S COOL.
- HEY, HEY, HEY.

20:07.300 --> 20:09.188
THANKS, HENRY.
THAT WAS REALLY NICE.

20:09.310 --> 20:10.197
YEAH.
- YOU'RE LIKE THE MAYOR.

20:10.310 --> 20:12.369
- [laughs] YEAH.
- THAT'S SO COOL.

20:12.480 --> 20:14.095
HEY, IS RYAN HERE?

20:14.210 --> 20:16.610
- NO. WHY?
- OH. HMM.

20:16.730 --> 20:19.039
WELL, HE'S, YOU KNOW,
AMBER'S NEW FLAME.

20:19.140 --> 20:21.028
THOUGHT I'D CHECK HIM OUT.

20:21.150 --> 20:23.175
- AMBER'S NEW FLAME?

20:23.290 --> 20:25.383
- YEAH, HE AND AMBER
STARTED DATING AFTER--

20:25.500 --> 20:26.899
I GUESS THEY HIT IT OFF
AT THE BASEBALL FIELD.

20:27.010 --> 20:28.454
HE DIDN'T TELL YOU?
- THEY'VE BEEN SEEING--

20:28.570 --> 20:30.288
NO, WE JUST HAD LUNCH
TOGETHER, RYAN--

20:30.400 --> 20:33.631
HE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,
AND WE TALKED ABOUT AMBER.

20:33.740 --> 20:34.638
HE DIDN'T TELL ME.

20:34.750 --> 20:37.742
- WELL, YOU'RE
AN INTIMIDATING GUY.

20:37.850 --> 20:39.886
YOU LIKE HIM THOUGH,
RIGHT, DAD?

20:39.990 --> 20:42.879
- IT'S, UH--
YEAH, UM--

20:43.000 --> 20:45.230
LET ME SHOW YOU MY OFFICE,
HONEY. COME HERE.

20:45.340 --> 20:46.853
- WELL, HOW EXACTLY
IS SHE DRIVING YOU CRAZY?

20:46.960 --> 20:48.302
- SHE'S A HOVERCRAFT.

20:48.410 --> 20:49.729
SHE'S IN THE KITCHEN.
SHE'S MOVING EVERYTHING AROUND

20:49.830 --> 20:51.991
IN THE HOUSE.
SHE'S SO FRUSTRATING TO ME.

20:52.110 --> 20:54.556
OH, BY THE WAY,
THE LESSINGS STOPPED BY TODAY,

20:54.660 --> 20:55.934
AND THEY BROUGHT A CHICKEN.
- ANOTHER CHICKEN.

20:56.040 --> 20:57.348
- THEY STAYED
FOR 2 1/2 HOURS.

20:57.460 --> 21:00.008
SHE TOOK NORA UPSTAIRS
WHILE I HAD TO SIT DOWNSTAIRS

21:00.120 --> 21:01.257
AND ENTERTAIN THEM.

21:01.360 --> 21:02.452
I HAD TO MAKE
PHIL LESSING TEA.

21:02.570 --> 21:04.629
IT'S JUST SO FRUSTRATING.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

21:04.740 --> 21:06.708
I FEEL LIKE A PRISONER
IN MY OWN HOME.

21:06.810 --> 21:08.744
- OH, SORRY. LISTEN, I'LL--
I'LL TALK TO HER.

21:08.850 --> 21:11.159
- [sighs] I JUST--I DON'T
WANT YOU TO DO THAT, OKAY?

21:11.270 --> 21:13.670
I MEAN, LOOK.
SHE'S FINE, SHE'S HELPFUL.

21:13.780 --> 21:17.546
SHE'S TRYING TO BE THERE
FOR ME. I JUST--

21:17.650 --> 21:18.924
IT'S FRUSTRATING TO ME,
HONEY,

21:19.030 --> 21:20.918
BECAUSE I DON'T LIKE
BEING TAKEN CARE OF.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.270
OKAY?
I'M NOT USED TO IT.

21:22.380 --> 21:24.371
I WANT TO TAKE CARE OF PEOPLE.
AND I FEEL JUST--

21:24.490 --> 21:26.958
I JUST--I FEEL HELPLESS
RIGHT NOW.

21:27.070 --> 21:28.514
YOU KNOW?
- OH, HONEY.

21:28.630 --> 21:32.214
- JUST I WISH--
[sighs]

21:32.320 --> 21:33.730
- WHAT IS IT, HON?
GO AHEAD.

21:33.840 --> 21:35.569
- I WANT TO BE ABLE
TO PICK UP MY BABY.

21:35.670 --> 21:38.138
I WANT TO BE ABLE
TO TAKE HER UPSTAIRS

21:38.260 --> 21:40.319
AND READ HER A BOOK
AT NAP TIME.

21:40.430 --> 21:42.159
I WANT TO BE ABLE TO NOT EAT
THIS CRAPPY FOOD

21:42.260 --> 21:45.536
THAT'S MAKING ME FEEL YUCKY AND
SUPPOSED TO BE HEALTHY FOR ME,

21:45.640 --> 21:48.359
OKAY?
AND I WANT MY MOM.

21:48.470 --> 21:50.574
I WANT MY OWN MOM TO CONSIDER ME
IMPORTANT ENOUGH

21:50.680 --> 21:52.989
TO GET ON A PLANE
AND COME HERE TO SEE ME.

21:53.100 --> 21:56.206
AND I KNOW I SOUND LIKE
I'M COMPLAINING RIGHT NOW,

21:56.310 --> 22:00.861
BUT I JUST SOMETIMES WISH
THAT THINGS WERE BACK TO NORMAL.

22:00.970 --> 22:03.279
AND I WISH THAT I COULD
JUST CRAWL UP IN A BALL

22:03.390 --> 22:07.417
AND CRY OVER IT,
BUT I CAN'T BECAUSE...

22:07.530 --> 22:10.875
BECAUSE YOUR MOTHER'S HERE.

22:12.600 --> 22:13.521
- I'M REALLY SORRY.

22:13.640 --> 22:16.427
- I'M SOR--
- KRISSY?

22:16.540 --> 22:19.566
- UM, I GOTTA GO.
I'M FINE.

22:19.680 --> 22:21.466
I'M JUST HAVING A MOMENT.
I LOVE YOU.

22:21.580 --> 22:25.095
- ALL RIGHT, LOVE YOU TOO.
BYE.

22:25.200 --> 22:28.067
[exhales]

23:01.480 --> 23:04.267
- HEY.
- HEY.

23:04.380 --> 23:05.824
- YOU ARE ALIVE.
NOT DYING.

23:05.930 --> 23:09.752
I HADN'T SEEN YOU AT SCHOOL,
SO I JUST ASSUMED

23:09.870 --> 23:11.349
YOU WERE SICK AND--
- YEAH, I'M FINE.

23:11.450 --> 23:12.314
I'M ACTUALLY GOING IN TODAY,
SO...

23:12.420 --> 23:13.626
- OH, YEAH?

23:13.730 --> 23:15.595
_ THANK YOU FOR THE BASKET,
BY THE WAY.

23:15.700 --> 23:16.359
- OH, YEAH.
- THAT WAS REALLY SWEET.

23:16.460 --> 23:17.597
- I JUST KIND OF LEFT IT.

23:17.700 --> 23:20.669
BUT I'M GLAD YOU GOT IT.
- YEAH.

23:20.770 --> 23:21.941
YOU KNOW, I SHOULD FINISH
GETTING READY.

23:22.050 --> 23:23.278
- YEAH, I JUST WANTED TO SAY
HEY, AND--

23:23.400 --> 23:26.426
- WHO'S THERE, AMES?

23:26.540 --> 23:28.121
- IT'S JUST MY FRIEND, DREW.
- OH, RIGHT.

23:28.230 --> 23:29.367
YOU KNOW,
I HEARD A LOT ABOUT YOU.

23:29.470 --> 23:31.290
- OH.

23:31.410 --> 23:34.743
- THIS IS JAKE.
- HEY.

23:36.410 --> 23:36.853
AH, SO SENIOR YEAR, HUH?

23:36.960 --> 23:38.404
- YEAH.

23:38.520 --> 23:39.646
- MAN, I WISH I WAS STILL
A SENIOR.

23:39.760 --> 23:41.785
I MEAN, DON'T GET ME WRONG.
I LOVE COLLEGE.

23:41.900 --> 23:43.379
BUT SENIOR YEAR IS
A SPECIAL KIND OF AWESOME.

23:43.490 --> 23:46.698
I ENW YOU, DUDE.
- OH, WOW. THANKS.

23:46.800 --> 23:49.143
I'LL JUST SEE YOU AT SCHOOL.
- OKAY.

23:49.250 --> 23:52.902
- HEY, YOU KNOW, I JUST DROPPED
BY TO TAKE AMES TO SCHOOL.

23:53.010 --> 23:55.456
WE CAN GIVE YOU A RIDE
IF YOU WANT.

23:55.570 --> 23:56.730
- IT'S--IT'S FINE.

23:56.840 --> 23:59.400
I HAVE MY BIKE, SO--
- YOU SURE?

23:59.500 --> 24:01.877
- YEAH.
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.

24:01.990 --> 24:02.945
- OKAY.

24:05.580 --> 24:08.640
[intense pop music]

24:27.810 --> 24:30.187
- I WAS THINKING
IT'D BE A GOOD IDEA

24:30.290 --> 24:31.518
IF I TOOK SYD OUT SO, YOU KNOW,
MIGUEL AND VICTOR

24:31.640 --> 24:33.847
COULD HAVE SOME TIME ALONE.

24:33.950 --> 24:35.463
THAT SOUND LIKE A GOOD IDEA?

24:35.570 --> 24:38.221
- YEAH.
YEAH, DEFINITELY.

24:38.330 --> 24:39.911
OH, THIS IS IT.
THIS ONE.

24:45.130 --> 24:47.758
- YEAH, HERE WE GO.

24:50.210 --> 24:50.858
- OH.

24:56.140 --> 24:57.619
- HEY, YOU MUST BE MIGUEL.

24:57.730 --> 24:58.970
I'M JOEL.
IT'S GOOD TO MEET YOU, BUDDY.

25:01.840 --> 25:05.287
- THERE HE IS.
- HEY.

25:05.400 --> 25:06.469
- THE RADIO'S NOT WORKING AGAIN?

25:06.570 --> 25:09.152
- JIMINY CHRISTMAS.
TWICE IN TWO DAYS.

25:09.260 --> 25:10.739
I THINK I SAW LESS OF YOU
WHEN YOU LIVED HERE.

25:10.850 --> 25:12.772
- WELL, I-I KNOW
HOW MUCH YOU MISS ME, SO--

25:12.890 --> 25:14.881
- WELL, I KIND OF MISS DREW
A LITTLE MORE.

25:14.990 --> 25:17.709
- THANKS, DAD.
APPRECIATE IT.

25:17.820 --> 25:20.539
HEY, THERE WASN'T ANYTHING ELSE
ABOUT RYAN AND AMBER

25:20.650 --> 25:22.823
THAT YOU WANTED TO TELL ME,
WAS THERE?

25:22.930 --> 25:24.921
I FEEL LIKE SOMETHING
WAS A LITTLE OFF.

25:25.040 --> 25:26.723
- NO, WELL, I--

25:26.830 --> 25:29.481
YEAH, HE JUST DIDN'T TELL ME
HE WAS DATING MY GRANDDAUGHTER.

25:29.590 --> 25:31.319
THAT KIND OF WAS SCREWED UP.

25:31.420 --> 25:32.557
- UH-OH.

25:32.660 --> 25:33.627
THAT'S IT, THOUGH?

25:33.730 --> 25:36.358
NOTHING ELSE TO WORRY ABOUT?

25:36.460 --> 25:38.212
- DAMN IT.
THIS ISN'T THE RIGHT TOOL.

25:38.320 --> 25:39.491
[chair clangs]
OUCH.

25:39.600 --> 25:41.215
WHAT'D I DO WITH THAT?
- DAD.

25:41.330 --> 25:41.876
[object clatters]

25:41.980 --> 25:44.187
- [exhales]

25:46.710 --> 25:49.087
I DON'T KNOW, SARAH.

25:49.200 --> 25:52.055
I MEAN, THE KID JUST GOT BACK
FROM AFGHANISTAN.

25:52.170 --> 25:56.618
YOU KNOW, HE'S BEEN IN A WAR.
GOT A LOT OF STUFF GOING ON.

25:56.720 --> 25:58.859
THAT'S NORMAL.
I MEAN...

25:58.970 --> 26:01.279
I WAS THE SAME WAY
WHEN I GOT BACK.

26:01.380 --> 26:07.455
JUST GONNA TAKE SOME TIME TO GET
SOME BALANCE IN HIS LIFE.

26:07.560 --> 26:10.688
[exhales]

26:10.810 --> 26:11.697
WELL, YOU KNOW WHEN YOU'RE
GOING THROUGH IT,

26:11.810 --> 26:15.940
IT'S USUALLY THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE

26:16.050 --> 26:17.460
AND THE ONES
THAT ARE CLOSEST TO YOU

26:17.570 --> 26:19.709
THAT GET HURT THE MOST.
THAT'S...

26:22.580 --> 26:24.400
- [sighs]

26:24.510 --> 26:27.923
- HE'S A GOOD KID, SARAH.

26:30.620 --> 26:36.206
[boys speaking Spanish]

26:38.490 --> 26:43.109
[both speaking Spanish]

26:43.220 --> 26:45.552
- [laughs]

26:45.670 --> 26:48.946
- [speaking Spanish]

26:49.050 --> 26:50.938
AH.

26:51.050 --> 26:53.018
- OH.
- [speaking Spanish]

26:57.020 --> 26:58.908
GRACIAS.

27:00.130 --> 27:05.022
[speaking Spanish]

27:06.480 --> 27:06.969
[ball thuds]

27:09.860 --> 27:15.480
- YEAH, I KNOW, MOM.
I UNDERSTAND.

27:15.590 --> 27:17.626
YEAH, IF ROY
HAS A KIDNEY STONE,

27:17.730 --> 27:20.619
I MEAN, THOSE CAN BE
PRETTY PAINFUL.

27:20.740 --> 27:23.322
SO IT'S PROBABLY
NOT THE BEST TIME

27:23.430 --> 27:26.012
FOR YOU TO BE OUT OF TOWN.

27:26.120 --> 27:28.680
SURE. I'LL JUST--
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

27:28.780 --> 27:30.987
- ALL RIGHT.

27:31.090 --> 27:32.739
I LOVE YOU.

27:33.680 --> 27:34.851
[phone beeps]

27:36.240 --> 27:37.025
- IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

27:37.130 --> 27:42.136
- YEAH.
IT'S JUST BAD TIMING.

27:42.240 --> 27:45.209
YOU KNOW, IT TURNS OUT
MY MOM'S NOT GONNA BE ABLE TO--

27:45.310 --> 27:46.789
TO GET OUT HERE RIGHT NOW.

27:46.900 --> 27:48.652
BUT SHE JUST WANTED TO SAY

27:48.770 --> 27:51.170
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR COVERING FOR HER.

27:51.290 --> 27:54.555
- I'M SORRY.

27:54.670 --> 27:56.285
I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU WANTED HER TO COME.

27:56.390 --> 27:57.357
- IT'S FINE.

27:57.460 --> 27:58.700
I MEAN, IT'S NOT A SURPRISE.

27:58.810 --> 28:01.358
SHE'S BEEN LIKE THIS FOR AS LONG
AS I CAN REMEMBER.

28:01.470 --> 28:02.698
YOU KNOW.

28:02.810 --> 28:04.084
I MEAN, I--

28:04.190 --> 28:10.265
I WANTED HER TO WANT
TO BE HERE.

28:12.720 --> 28:13.709
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M ACT UALLY--

28:13.830 --> 28:15.923
[sighs]
I'D LIKE TO GO GET MAX.

28:16.030 --> 28:17.588
- OH, NO, I WAS JUST
GOING TO PICK HIM UP NOW.

28:17.690 --> 28:18.543
- IT'S FINE.

28:18.660 --> 28:19.376
HONESTLY, I'VE BEEN COOPED UP

28:19.490 --> 28:20.582
IN THIS HOUSE FOR A WEEK.

28:20.690 --> 28:23.079
AND I JUST--I'M--I'M
JUST WANTING TO GET OUT.

28:23.180 --> 28:25.102
- AND YOU THINK YOU'RE OKAY
TO DRIVE?

28:25.220 --> 28:29.805
- CAMILLE, I'M COMPLETELY FINE.
OKAY?

28:29.910 --> 28:30.979
I'M ABLE TO PICK UP
MY DAUGHTER,

28:31.080 --> 28:32.593
I'M ABLE TO PICK UP MY SON
FROM SCHOOL.

28:32.710 --> 28:33.802
I CAN MAKE MY OWN TEA.

28:33.910 --> 28:35.389
I KNOW HOW TO TAKE CARE
OF EVERYTHING.

28:35.500 --> 28:37.320
JUST--CAN I HAVE THE KEYS?

28:37.430 --> 28:39.125
- OF COURSE.

28:51.210 --> 28:53.030
[door closes]

28:59.630 --> 29:05.489
[overlapping chatter]

29:05.600 --> 29:08.160
- HEY.
- HI.

29:09.260 --> 29:12.013
- LOOK, I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT EARLIER.

29:12.120 --> 29:13.985
THAT WAS REALLY AWKWARD
FOR ALL OF US.

29:14.090 --> 29:16.024
- YEAH, WAS THAT
YOUR CAMP FRIEND?

29:16.130 --> 29:18.917
- UM, WELL,
WE KIND OF MET THERE.

29:19.030 --> 29:23.399
- WAS HE LIKE A LIFEGUARD
OR SOMETHING?

29:23.520 --> 29:25.203
ISN'T HE, LIKE, EMBARRASSED?

29:25.310 --> 29:27.232
HE'S LIKE A COLLEGE GUY
DATING SOME HIGH SCHOOL GIRL.

29:27.350 --> 29:31.798
I MEAN, HE LOOKS LIKE 30.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:31.900 --> 29:33.765
ISN'T IT ILLEGAL ALSO
ON TOP OF IT?

29:33.870 --> 29:34.768
- WOW. REALLY?
- IT PROBABLY IS ILLEGAL.

29:34.870 --> 29:36.974
- DREW, I'M SORRY.

29:37.080 --> 29:38.559
AND I MEAN,
I KNOW THAT THIS MORNING

29:38.670 --> 29:39.284
WAS PROBABLY REALLY HARD
FOR YOU.

29:39.390 --> 29:40.766
- ALL RIGHT, WHATEVER.

29:40.880 --> 29:42.598
DON'T GIVE ME THAT,
ALL RIGHT?

29:42.710 --> 29:44.325
ENOUGH BAD STUFF
IS HAPPENING TO ME.

29:44.430 --> 29:45.874
I'M PRETTY MUCH USED TO
IT AT THIS POINT, SO--

29:45.990 --> 29:47.981
- WHY? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

29:48.090 --> 29:50.957
- NOTHING. MY MOM DECIDED
TO MOVE IN WITH MR. CYR.

29:51.060 --> 29:52.129
SO YOU KNOW,
NOW I LIVE WITH HIM

29:52.230 --> 29:53.743
IN THIS TWO-BEDROOM APARTMENT,

29:53.860 --> 29:55.646
AND WE FOUND OUT
MY AUNT HAS CANCER.

29:55.750 --> 29:57.991
- WHAT?
- YEAH, MY AUNT KRISTINA.

29:58.100 --> 30:00.989
SHE HAS CANCER,
SO IT'S SERIOUS.

30:01.100 --> 30:05.628
AND THE BASKET THAT I GAVE YOU
WAS HER CANCER BASKET.

30:05.730 --> 30:06.890
SO YOU CAN THANK HER
FOR THAT ONE.

30:07.010 --> 30:08.409
I GOTTA GO.
WHATEVER.

30:08.530 --> 30:09.246
[school bell rings]

30:15.150 --> 30:18.222
- SURPRISE.
- YOU'RE DRIVING.

30:18.330 --> 30:20.082
- YUP.

30:20.190 --> 30:21.430
- YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE DRIVING.

30:21.540 --> 30:22.609
DAD SAID.
- I KNOW.

30:27.060 --> 30:28.857
- AND YOU'RE EATING ICE CREAM.
- MM-HMM.

30:28.960 --> 30:31.952
- DAD SAYS YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO DO THAT EITHER.

30:34.900 --> 30:36.231
- THAT'S
AN IT'S-IT SANDWICH TREAT.

30:36.350 --> 30:37.419
HERE'S HOW
THIS IS GONNA GO DOWN.

30:37.520 --> 30:40.796
YOU DID NOT SEE ME
EAT THIS ICE CREAM CONE.

30:40.900 --> 30:41.935
AND YOU DID NOT SEE ME DRIVING.

30:42.040 --> 30:44.349
ARE YOU LISTENING?
- YEAH.

30:44.460 --> 30:46.837
- WHAT HAPPENS HERE STAYS HERE.
OKAY?

30:46.940 --> 30:49.215
- SO IT'S LIKE IN VEGAS?
- KIND OF.

30:49.330 --> 30:51.389
AND IF DAD ASKS,
GRANDMA PICKED YOU UP.

30:51.500 --> 30:52.592
I DID NOT PICK YOU UP.

30:52.710 --> 30:54.257
YOU GOT IT?

30:54.360 --> 30:58.501
- WHAT DO I GET
IF I SAY THAT?

30:58.610 --> 31:01.499
[light music throughout]

31:17.730 --> 31:21.803
[door opens]

31:21.910 --> 31:23.491
[door closes]

31:23.600 --> 31:26.080
- HEY.
- HI.

31:26.190 --> 31:28.806
- SO, HOW'D IT GO?

31:28.920 --> 31:31.605
- REALLY, REALLY WELL.

31:31.710 --> 31:32.916
- YEAH?

31:33.020 --> 31:36.228
- YEAH. IT WAS KIND
OF AMAZING, ACTUALLY.

31:36.340 --> 31:37.159
HE WAS SO HAPPY.

31:37.270 --> 31:41.161
I MEAN, HE WAS LIKE
A DIFFERENT KID.

31:41.270 --> 31:44.205
HE WAS SO ENGAGED,
AND HE WAS HAVING--

31:44.310 --> 31:46.926
HE WAS HAVING A WONDERFUL TIME.
IT WAS REALLY SOMETHING.

31:47.040 --> 31:49.554
[sighs]

31:51.870 --> 31:53.007
- WHAT?

31:55.600 --> 31:59.218
- BUT I WISH THAT WE COULD
BRING THAT OUT IN HIM.

31:59.330 --> 32:03.391
I WISH THAT WE COULD
MAKE HIM THAT HAPPY.

32:03.500 --> 32:05.127
I REALLY THOUGHT THAT
WE WERE MAKING PROGRESS...

32:05.230 --> 32:06.811
[laughs]
- WE ARE, HONEY.

32:06.920 --> 32:07.602
- WE ARE.

32:07.710 --> 32:10.782
BUT IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

32:10.890 --> 32:12.198
THERE'S A WHOLE WORLD
INSIDE HIM.

32:12.300 --> 32:14.302
WE'RE JUST NOT GETTING
IN THERE.

32:14.410 --> 32:18.710
AND I WANT TO SEE
THAT VERSION OF HIM.

32:18.830 --> 32:22.789
ALL THE TIME.

32:22.900 --> 32:26.722
- WE WILL.

32:26.840 --> 32:32.665
- [whistling]

32:32.770 --> 32:33.805
HEY.
- HEY.

32:33.910 --> 32:35.116
- WHAT ARE YOU STILL
DOING HERE?

32:35.220 --> 32:38.496
- UM, UH, KRISTINA
WENT TO SLEEP EARLY,

32:38.610 --> 32:40.009
AND MOM AND DAD ARE WATCHING
MAX AND NORA.

32:40.130 --> 32:42.360
SO I JUST WANTED TO CATCH UP,
YOU KNOW. YOU KNOW WHAT?

32:42.470 --> 32:43.949
I HAVE SOME QUESTIONS HERE
FOR YOU

32:44.060 --> 32:45.812
ABOUT THESE BOOKINGS
AND EXPENSES RIGHT HERE.

32:45.920 --> 32:46.602
CAN YOU TAKE A LOOK
AT THOSE FOR ME?

32:46.720 --> 32:47.994
- ADAM.
- WHAT?

32:48.100 --> 32:48.919
- COULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR

32:49.030 --> 32:50.190
AND JUST STAND UP FOR A SECOND?

32:50.310 --> 32:51.754
- YOU NEED TO LOOK AT THESE.

32:51.860 --> 32:52.781
- I WILL LOOK AT THOSE TOMORROW,

32:52.900 --> 32:54.162
BUT YOU NEED TO STAND UP
RIGHT NOW.

32:54.280 --> 32:55.440
WE NEED TO GO OUT TO A BAR
AND GET YOU A COCKTAIL.

32:55.550 --> 32:57.370
- NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

32:57.490 --> 32:58.559
THAT IS THE LAST THING
I NEED TO DO.

32:58.660 --> 32:59.627
- HAVE YOU LOOKED
AT YOURSELF RECENTLY?

32:59.730 --> 33:00.833
- NO, I HAVE NOT.

33:00.940 --> 33:01.793
- YOU'RE A MAN
WHO'S IN DESPERATE NEED

33:01.910 --> 33:02.695
OF A COCKTAIL.
LET'S GO, NOW.

33:02.800 --> 33:03.971
- I'M ON A NO-ALCOHOL DIET.

33:04.080 --> 33:06.287
I'M IN SOLIDARITY WITH KRISTINA
RIGHT NOW.

33:06.390 --> 33:07.834
OKAY? SO I'M NOT--
I'M NOT GOING OUT TO A BAR.

33:07.950 --> 33:09.144
- I PROMISE YOU SHE WILL NEVER
FIND OUT.

33:09.260 --> 33:12.115
AND ALL THIS STUFF WILL BE
WAITING FOR YOU TOMORROW.

33:12.230 --> 33:13.458
YOU CAN DO INFOTHEN' OKAY?

33:13.570 --> 33:14.673
- I'LL TELL YOU WHAT
I'M GONNA DO.

33:14.780 --> 33:17.601
- WHAT?
- ONE-TIME OFFER ONLY.

33:17.710 --> 33:18.608
I WILL PAY.

33:18.720 --> 33:19.197
- [mockingly gasps]

33:19.300 --> 33:21.359
- IT'S THAT SERIOUS.

33:21.480 --> 33:24.472
- DO I REALLY LBEK THAT BAD?

33:24.580 --> 33:27.140
- I TRY TO HELP OUT KRISTINA
BY HAVING MOM COME OVER,

33:27.240 --> 33:29.481
AND THEN SHE GETS UPSET,
AND I GOTTA GO CALL MOM.

33:29.590 --> 33:30.750
AND SAY, "LISTEN, WE WANT YOU
TO STOP MOVING STUFF

33:30.870 --> 33:32.622
AROUND THE CUPBOARD."
- HEY, MY FRIEND. TWO BEERS.

33:32.730 --> 33:35.278
- EXCUSE ME.

33:35.390 --> 33:36.652
AND YOU KNOW, I CAN HEAR HURT
FEELINGS ON THE PHONE.

33:36.770 --> 33:37.862
SHE GETS ALL QUIET.
I'M JUST SAYING, "MOM,

33:37.980 --> 33:39.663
"WE APPRECIATE
WHAT YOU'RE DOING,

33:39.770 --> 33:41.829
BUT WE JUST DON'T WANT YOU
MOVING STUFF AROUND THE HOUSE."

33:41.950 --> 33:43.212
YOU KNOW. IT'S ALL IT'S--

33:43.330 --> 33:45.184
EXCUSE ME. COULD YOU PLEASE
STOP BUMPING INTO ME?

33:45.290 --> 33:46.496
- IT'S CROWDED.
- WELL, IT'S NOT THAT CROWDED.

33:46.610 --> 33:49.363
- SO WHY DON'T YOU RELAX?
- I'M NOT BUMPING INTO YOU.

33:49.470 --> 33:51.324
- JERK.
- OH, I'M THE JERK?

33:51.440 --> 33:52.509
- OKAY, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
HEY, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

33:52.610 --> 33:53.952
- JUST TRY BEING A LITTLE MORE
CONSIDERATE.

33:54.060 --> 33:55.641
- GO BACK TO YOUR OKTOBERFEST
THERE WITH YOUR BEER STEIN.

33:55.750 --> 33:56.921
LET'S GO DOWN HERE.

33:57.030 --> 33:58.258
- PEOPLE ARE REALLY
STARTING TO PISS ME OFF.

33:58.380 --> 34:00.996
- OKAY. HERE WE GO.
HERE'S TWO STOOLS.

34:01.100 --> 34:02.203
- WALK OUT OF MY HOUSE
THE OTHER DAY,

34:02.310 --> 34:04.175
GOING TO THE CAR,
THE NEIGHBOR COMES UP TO ME,

34:04.280 --> 34:05.486
SAYS, "ADAM, I JUST WANT YOU
TO REMEMBER

34:05.590 --> 34:07.239
GOD ONLY GIVES YOU
WHAT YOU CAN HANDLE."

34:07.350 --> 34:09.318
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

34:09.420 --> 34:11.729
IS THAT SUPPOSED TO HELP ME
WATCH MY WIFE SUFFER?

34:17.640 --> 34:20.188
SHE STARTS
CHEMOTHERAPY TOMORROW.

34:23.500 --> 34:28.403
YOU SHOULD SEE THESE WOMEN
AFTER THEY'VE BEEN IN CHEMO.

34:31.270 --> 34:33.830
THEY LOOK LIKE GHOSTS.

34:37.100 --> 34:41.628
JUST, MAN, THE THOUGHT
OF KRISTINA HAVING TO...

34:41.730 --> 34:43.277
GO THROUGH THAT IS--

34:46.980 --> 34:50.734
IT'S SCARY.

34:50.840 --> 34:53.491
IT'S REALLY SCARY, CROS.

34:55.670 --> 35:00.607
[overlapping chatter]

35:07.960 --> 35:11.339
[distant sirens wail]

35:30.020 --> 35:32.363
- HEY, BUDDY.

35:32.470 --> 35:34.779
- HEY.

35:34.890 --> 35:35.914
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP?

35:36.030 --> 35:38.225
- [sighs] OH.

35:38.340 --> 35:41.229
I COULDN'T SLEEP.

35:41.340 --> 35:43.649
- YOU OKAY?
- MM-HMM.

35:46.760 --> 35:49.627
- IS THERE ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

35:51.970 --> 35:55.212
- YOU SHOULD GO BACK TO SLEEP.

35:55.320 --> 35:57.527
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

35:57.630 --> 36:01.077
[Neil Halstead's
Full Moon Rising]

36:01.190 --> 36:06.366
- YOU WOULDN'T TEAR LOVE
ABOVE FOR US

36:08.710 --> 36:14.501
STAND BY THE DOOR
IN YOUR RED DRESS

36:15.960 --> 36:19.134
YOU'RE JUST A LITTLE GIRL

36:19.240 --> 36:22.038
HIDING IN THE DARK

36:22.140 --> 36:25.587
TELL ME,
HOW DOES IT FEEL

36:25.700 --> 36:26.928
LIGHTS GO OFF

36:27.040 --> 36:28.382
[door opens]

36:28.490 --> 36:29.388
- HEY.

36:29.490 --> 36:30.104
I WAS JUST WRITING YOU
THIS NUMBER.

36:30.220 --> 36:31.448
THIS IS THE MAIN DESK

36:31.560 --> 36:33.596
'CAUSE WE CAN'T HAVE
OUR CELL PHONES

36:33.700 --> 36:35.327
IN THE TREATMENT ROOM,
SO CALL US THERE.

36:35.430 --> 36:36.636
I'M GONNA PUT THE CAR SEAT
IN YOUR CAR

36:36.740 --> 36:38.082
IN CASE YOU AND NORA
WANT TO GO SOMEPLACE.

36:38.190 --> 36:40.750
- UH, GOOD IDEA.

36:40.850 --> 36:42.329
GOOD MORNING.
- HEY.

36:42.440 --> 36:43.156
GOOD MORNING. HOW ARE YOU?
- GOOD.

36:43.270 --> 36:44.191
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

36:44.300 --> 36:47.952
- I'M FEELING READY TO GO.

36:48.060 --> 36:49.163
ADAM MADE PANCAKES
IF YOU'RE HUNGRY.

36:49.270 --> 36:52.512
- OH, I ATE. THANKS.
MAYBE COFFEE LATER.

36:52.620 --> 36:54.133
- YEAH.
THERE'S PLENTY OF COFFEE.

36:54.240 --> 36:56.515
- UM, I BROUGHT YOU SOMETHING.

36:56.620 --> 36:59.066
REMEMBER I TOLD YOU ABOUT
MY FRIEND

36:59.180 --> 37:00.932
WHO HAD JUST GONE
THROUGH CHEMO?

37:01.040 --> 37:03.656
SHE GAVE ME THIS
TO GIVE TO YOU.

37:03.770 --> 37:06.284
HER AUNT WHO HAD BEEN THROUGH
THE SAME THING

37:06.390 --> 37:08.426
GAVE IT TO HER.

37:08.530 --> 37:12.182
SO IT'S BEEN PASSED
FROM PERSON TO PERSON.

37:12.290 --> 37:14.770
AND YOU WILL BE
THE SEVENTH PERSON

37:14.880 --> 37:17.257
TO WEAR THIS DURING CHEMO.

37:17.370 --> 37:19.463
I UNDERSTAND IT GETS
REALLY COLD.

37:19.580 --> 37:23.437
AND THAT'S WARM AND COZY.
IT'S ALSO--

37:23.550 --> 37:25.063
IT GOES ON AND OFF REAL EASY.

37:25.170 --> 37:27.684
YOU KNOW, JUST IN CASE.

37:27.790 --> 37:31.863
- THIS IS REALLY THOUGHTFUL.
THANK YOU.

37:35.350 --> 37:36.999
- KRISTINA.

37:37.110 --> 37:38.338
- [sniffles]

37:38.460 --> 37:43.147
- YOU KNOW WHEN ADAM
FIRST BROUGHT YOU HOME

37:43.260 --> 37:44.704
TO MEET ME,

37:44.810 --> 37:47.358
I REALLY DIDN'T THINK
YOU WERE RIGHT FOR HIM.

37:47.470 --> 37:48.698
- [laughs]
REALLY?

37:51.640 --> 37:52.538
- I'VE NEVER BEEN SO HAPPY

37:52.640 --> 37:56.406
TO BE SO WRONG
ABOUT ANYONE.

37:57.270 --> 37:59.921
- [whispers]
THANKS.

38:00.030 --> 38:03.306
- AND I KNOW I'M NOT YOUR MOM.

38:03.410 --> 38:06.379
I WOULD NEVER TRY
TO REPLACE HER.

38:06.490 --> 38:08.060
BUT I LOVE YOU, KRISSY.

38:08.180 --> 38:12.037
I'M HERE FOR YOU.

38:12.150 --> 38:14.618
I'D DO ANYTHING FOR YOU.

38:16.290 --> 38:18.804
ANYTHING.

38:22.850 --> 38:24.602
- THANK YOU.

38:34.270 --> 38:35.373
[sniffles]

38:35.480 --> 38:37.994
[knock on door]

38:38.100 --> 38:39.579
- HEY.
- HEY.

38:39.690 --> 38:41.999
- SORRY TO JUST SHOW UP
LIKE THIS.

38:42.110 --> 38:43.998
I CALLED YOUR CELL PHONE,
BUT YOU DIDN'T ANSWER.

38:44.110 --> 38:46.829
- YEAH.
UM, SORRY.

38:46.940 --> 38:48.350
- CAN I COME IN?

38:49.150 --> 38:50.071
- UM...

38:50.180 --> 38:54.526
SURE, AMY.

38:55.710 --> 38:59.703
- WOW. SO THIS
IS WHERE MR. CYR LIVES.

38:59.820 --> 39:01.128
- YEAH.

39:01.230 --> 39:02.982
- ALL OF MY FRIENDS WOULD DIE
IF THEY KNEW I WAS IN HERE.

39:03.090 --> 39:04.261
THEY'RE ALL IN LOVE WITH HIM.

39:04.370 --> 39:06.167
- YUP. EVERYONE.

39:06.270 --> 39:07.749
EVERYBODY LOVES HIM.

39:07.860 --> 39:10.067
I-I JUST WANT TO SAY
I'M SORRY

39:10.170 --> 39:11.376
REALLY QUICK
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

39:11.480 --> 39:14.540
- IT'S OKAY.
I GET IT.

39:14.660 --> 39:18.824
AND DREW,
IF YOU NEED SPACE,

39:18.940 --> 39:19.929
JUST TELL ME.

39:20.040 --> 39:23.487
I MEAN, I WOULD REALLY LIKE
TO BE FRIENDS.

39:23.600 --> 39:25.283
BUT IF YOU DON'T,
I UNDERSTAND.

39:25.390 --> 39:30.009
AND ANYWAY, I JUST

39:30.120 --> 39:32.771
WELL, I WAS JUST STOPPING BY
'CAUSE I WANTED TO TELL YOU

39:32.880 --> 39:34.563
THAT I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT YOUR AUNT.

39:34.680 --> 39:39.151
- OH.
YEAH, THANKS.

39:39.270 --> 39:40.430
- IT'S SO HORRIBLE.

39:40.550 --> 39:41.403
IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

39:41.510 --> 39:44.229
- I MEAN, I HOPE SO.

39:44.340 --> 39:46.513
WE ALL HOPE SO.

39:51.970 --> 39:54.484
UM...

39:54.590 --> 39:56.239
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE I--

39:56.350 --> 39:59.239
LIKE, I FEEL LIKE
I SHOULD DO SOMETHING.

39:59.360 --> 40:01.351
YOU KNOW, LIKE, YOU KNOW,
I FEEL LIKE

40:01.460 --> 40:03.325
I WANT TO HELP SOMEHOW.

40:03.430 --> 40:05.534
BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW TO.

40:05.640 --> 40:08.222
THERE'S NOTHING FOR ME TO DO,
YOU KNOW.

40:08.330 --> 40:12.949
AND I JUST KIND OF FEEL GUILTY.

40:13.060 --> 40:13.981
- DREW.

40:14.100 --> 40:20.164
LOOK, YOU'RE--
YOU'RE AMAZING, AND...

40:20.270 --> 40:22.682
YOU'LL FIND A WAY.

40:24.970 --> 40:28.451
- IT'S JUST SO UPSETTING,
YOU KNOW.

40:28.560 --> 40:32.109
SHE'S STARTING CHEMO TODAY.

40:32.220 --> 40:37.567
[Alabama Shakes' Alone]

40:37.670 --> 40:39.535
- OH, ARE YOU SCARED
TO WEAR YOUR HEART

40:39.640 --> 40:43.019
OUT ON YOUR SLEEVE

40:43.130 --> 40:49.956
'CAUSE I'M SCARED
THE BOMB GONNA TAKE ME AWAY

40:50.060 --> 40:52.540
- OH, BUT I REALLY
DON'T KNOW

40:52.650 --> 40:57.166
WHAT I GOT TO SAY

40:57.280 --> 40:59.965
OH OH, WELL

41:00.070 --> 41:01.276
UN HOMBRE.

41:01.380 --> 41:07.148
HOMBRE.

41:07.250 --> 41:08.319
NINO.

41:08.430 --> 41:10.216
UN NINO.

41:10.320 --> 41:13.357
- OH OH OH

41:13.470 --> 41:15.847
WELL, THAT'S JUST WHY

41:15.950 --> 41:18.157
YOU AND ME

41:18.260 --> 41:19.989
'CAUSE I'M SCARED

41:20.090 --> 41:24.789
THE STORM'S GONNA
TAKE ME AWAY

41:24.890 --> 41:28.098
OH, BUT I REALLY
DON'T KNOW

41:28.200 --> 41:31.033
